article.description: Sacramento State 93, San Jose Christian C 58
article.headline: Sacramento State 93, San Jose Christian C 58
article.linkText: Sacramento State 93, San Jose Christian C 58
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sophomore Loren Leath had a career-high 28 points, including six 3-point shots, to lead Sacramento State over William Jessup 93-58 on Wednesday night. Angel Alamo had 14 points, 10 rebounds, three blocked shots and three steals in 22 minutes for the Hornets (3-3), who have beaten the Warriors four straight times. Matt Kristoff's 14 points, Joseph Mitchell's 12, and Lucas Bichard's 11 led William Jessup (2-5). Sacramento State had their biggest margin of the game at 38 points after Donald Thomas hit a lay up with 2:09 left. The Hornets held the Warriors to 6-for-25 shooting from the floor in the first half. Leath had 15 points, and Roderick Adams dished out six assists to put Sacramento State up 40-17 at the half.
